attributes.Long form description: The student grabs the GoPro and inspects it to find the battery door but he has trouble so the instructor helps him. The student tries to open the battery door by pulling it but he does it the wrong way so he keeps trying until he makes it. Then he grabs the old battery and pulls out to introduce a new one. Next, he searches for the micro SD card slot but he can't find it so the instructor helps him. The student opens the battery door and takes out the battery to find the micro SD card. He grabs the old micro SD card, takes it out, and inserts a new one. Then the instructor tells him to turn on the GoPro so the student presses the top button but that's incorrect so the instructor corrects him and the student presses the left button and turns on the GoPro correctly. Then the student turns off the GoPro by holding the left button. Next, the student approaches the strap and inspects it, also opens the mount of the GoPro, and aligns it with the mount peg of the strap. The student screws the strap with the GoPro. Then the instructor tells him to detach the GoPro from the strap and change it to the handheld grip so he unscrews the strap and detaches it from the GoPro. He approaches to the handheld grip and inspects it, then he aligns the mount of the GoPro with the handheld grip and starts to screw. The instructor tells the student to detach the handheld grip so he unscrews the GoPro and closes the mount. Then puts all the pieces on the table.
